---------------------------------------------------------------------------
## Hit Dice (HD) ##
---------------------------------------------------------------------------

These determine how many [Hit Points (HP)] a character has. Different [Class]es have different types of Hit Dice, e.g. d8, d10.

dnd: ph12
subtype: char


---------------------------------------------------------------------------
## Hit Points (HP) ##
---------------------------------------------------------------------------

Represents health. At first level, Hit Points = max of [Hit Dice] + Constitution Modifier (see [Ability Modifiers]). At subsequent levels, roll [Hit Dice] and add that with Constitution Modifier to obtain new HP, OR add half of [Hit Dice] max +1 + Constitution Modifier (avoids randomness).

When reach 0 or below HP, can be [Dead] or [Unconscious] - dead if get [Massive Damage] (if remaining damage >= HP max). When Unconscious must make [Saving Throw]s against Death [see ph197]

dnd: ph12,197
subtype: char


---------------------------------------------------------------------------
## Level ##
---------------------------------------------------------------------------

Character Levels are based on [Experience Points (XP)] - as reach higher levels gain more abilities, skills, spells, etc.

dnd: ph15
subtype: char


---------------------------------------------------------------------------
## Race ##
---------------------------------------------------------------------------

Establishes fundamental qualities that exist throughout character's life. Determines [Hit Dice], additions to [Ability Scores], etc. E.g. Human, Elf, Halfling, Dragonborn, Drow.

dnd: ph17
subtype: char


---------------------------------------------------------------------------
## Speed ##
---------------------------------------------------------------------------

How far can travel in one combat Round (6 seconds) with short bursts of energy. Normal movement and travel pace is slower.

